</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Sustainable development</strong> - Development that meets the needs of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Biodiversity</strong> - The variety of plant and animal life in the world or in a particular habitat, regarded as important and desirable.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Environmental regulation</strong> - Legal rules and requirements that govern how businesses can interact with the environment.



</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-41_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-42_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-43_ pf-heading-1-h3">DEFRA's core responsibilities</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Environmental protection</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-47_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">DEFRA is responsible for setting and enforcing standards for air and water quality, managing waste, and combating climate change. The department develops strategies to reduce carbon emissions and promotes the use of renewable energy sources.







































</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-49_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Food and farming</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-51_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The department ensures that food produced and sold in the UK meets high safety standards. It supports farmers through subsidies and grants, promotes sustainable agricultural practices, and works to improve animal health and welfare.







































</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-53_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Rural development</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-55_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">DEFRA's rural development policies aim to enhance the quality of life in rural areas. This includes improving infrastructure, supporting rural businesses, and ensuring access to essential services such as healthcare and education.






































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-57_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-58_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practices for implementation</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-61_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Compliance with environmental regulations</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-63_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-64_ pf-text-1"><strong>Adopt sustainable practices</strong> - Businesses should implement energy-efficient processes, reduce waste, and use sustainable materials.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-66_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular audits</strong> - Conduct regular environmental audits to ensure compliance with DEFRA regulations.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-68_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training and education</strong> - Provide ongoing training for staff on environmental regulations and sustainability practices.




</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-70_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Ensuring food safety and quality</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-72_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-73_ pf-text-1"><strong>Implement food safety management systems </strong>- Adopting systems such as HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Points) helps in managing food safety risks.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-75_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular inspections and testing</strong> - conduct routine inspections and testing to ensure compliance with food safety standards.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-77_ pf-text-1"><strong>Traceability systems</strong> - Maintain robust traceability systems to track the origin and movement of food products.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-79_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Promoting rural development</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-81_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-82_ pf-text-1"><strong>Community engagement </strong>- Engage with local communities to understand their needs and develop tailored support programs.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-84_ pf-text-1"><strong>Invest in infrastructure</strong> - Support the development of essential infrastructure such as roads, broadband, and public services.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-86_ pf-text-1"><strong>Support local businesses</strong> - Provide grants and support to rural businesses to stimulate economic growth and job creation.

